@database "HelpManager Help"
@$VER HelpManager Version1.0
@Author (c) 1997,98 by Lars Unger

@NODE MAIN "HelpManager - Help Guide"

@{JCENTER}
@{b}@{u} Helpmanager @{uu}@{ub}
@{i} Version 1.0 @{ui}
@{i} (c) 1997,98 by Lars Unger @{ui}
@{JLEFT}

@{u}  Help  @{uu}


 @{i} View Index @{ui}

     This link takes you to your index guide.
    @{b} You`ve to create one first with "Update Index" ! @{ub}

 @{" Search ...    " link "search"}



@{u} Preferences @{uu}

 @{b} You should create a new index guide with @{i} Update Index @{ui} every
  time you change something here. @{ub}


 @{" Add/Delete path " link "addepa"}

 @{i} Set pattern @{ui}

     You`re able to choose between 9 patterns for the files, which
     will be recognized as "Helpfiles" by Helpmanager.
    @{b} Default is .guide & .doc & .dok @{ub}

 @{i} Update Index @{ui}

    This link will create a new index guide. If you`ve add/delete a path
    and/or use Helpmanager for the first time you should use this.


@{JCENTER}
@{"Back to Helpmanager" link "ffds:hm.guide/MAIN"}

@{i} HelpManager is part of FileFindDatabaseSystem @{ui}
@{" FFDS " link "ffds:ffds.guide/MAIN"}


@ENDNODE
@NODE search "HM-Help: Search ..."
@NEXT addepa
@PREV MAIN


@{JCENTER}
@{b}@{u} HelpManager @{uu}@{ub}
@{i} Version 1.0 @{ui}
@{i} (c) 1997,98 by Lars Unger @{ui}
@{JLEFT}

@{u}  Help: Search ... @{uu}

  @{i} New search @{ui}

  Every search creates an result guide in your temporary directory (t:).
  With this button you`re able to create a new one. The modes INDEX and
  FFDS are possible. INDEX: search in the given help-pathes from Helpmanager.
  FFDS: search in FFDS databases and filter the result.

  @{i} View Result @{ui}

  Switch to the result guide (if exists one).
  @{i} Warning @{ui} If you don`t leave the guide from Main Menu, the result
  guide will not be deleted and stay in t: (maybe wasting your ram:).

  @{" Back to Main Menu " link "MAIN"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE addepa "HM-Help: Add/Delete path ..."
@NEXT MAIN
@PREV search

@{JCENTER}
@{b}@{u} HelpManager @{uu}@{ub}
@{i} Version 1.0 @{ui}
@{i} (c) 1997,98 by Lars Unger @{ui}
@{JLEFT}

@{u}  Help: Add/Delete path ... @{uu}

  @{i} Add path    @{ui}

  You can choose a path to add to the path list of Helpmanager. All paths are
  scanned for "Helpfiles" by @{i} Update Index @{ui}.
  @{b} Default path is help: @{ub}

  @{i} Delete path @{ui}

  You can delete a path from the path list.
  @{b} Warning! You should at least have one path in the list. @{ub}

  @{" Back to Main Menu " link "MAIN"}

@ENDNODE
